---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import TimeLineElement from "../components/cv/TimeLine.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Resume" sideBarActiveItemID="cv">
  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Profile</div>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-10 text-justify">
    I'm Jack Zhang, a Computer Engineering undergraduate at the University of Illinois Urbana-Champaign, minoring in Statistics. My background combines strong mathematical foundations with hands-on experience in machine learning, full-stack development, and algorithmic fairness. I’ve conducted research on speaker-invariant representation learning and fairness-aware ML under distribution shift, and contributed to AI-driven systems in finance, healthcare, and e-commerce domains.
  </div>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Education</div>
  </div>

  <div class="time-line-container grid gap-4 mb-10">
    <TimeLineElement
      title="University of Illinois at Urbana-Champaign"
      subtitle="2022 to 2026 · B.S. in Computer Engineering, Minor in Statistics · Champaign, United States"
    />
  </div>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Experience</div>
  </div>

  <div class="time-line-container mb-10">
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Research Intern — Multimodal Biometric Representation Learning"
      subtitle="May 2025 to Present · Hangzhou"
    >
      Built speaker recognition models using speaker-invariant deep residual frameworks. Improved robustness to background noise and inter-speaker variability for real-world audio-based identification.
    </TimeLineElement>

    <TimeLineElement
      title="Research Intern — Fairness-Aware Machine Learning under Distribution Shift"
      subtitle="May 2023 to Aug 2023 · Remote"
    >
      Developed fairness-regularized MLPs using PyTorch. Proposed Shifty-Pro algorithm to improve demographic parity and generalization across population drift scenarios, achieving a 42.7% improvement in fairness metrics.
    </TimeLineElement>

    <TimeLineElement
      title="Data Analyst — Shanghai Artificial Intelligence Laboratory"
      subtitle="May 2023 to Aug 2023 · Shanghai"
    >
      Built hospital cost prediction models using multivariate linear regression. Developed credit card fraud detection pipelines with logistic regression. Applied YOLOv8-based object detection for sports analytics.
    </TimeLineElement>

    <TimeLineElement
      title="Full-Stack Developer — E-Commerce Inventory Optimization System"
      subtitle="Feb 2025 to May 2025 · Champaign"
    >
      Led backend (Flask + SQL) and frontend (React) development for an intelligent order-tracking and analytics system. Designed transaction logic, complex queries, and user interfaces for real-time insights.
    </TimeLineElement>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Certifications</div>
  </div>

  <ul class="list-disc mx-6 mb-10 grid gap-2">
    <li>
      <a href="https://www.ets.org/toefl" target="_blank">TOEFL 109</a>
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href="https://www.coursera.org/specializations/deep-learning" target="_blank">Deep Learning Specialization (in progress)</a>
    </li>
  </ul>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Skills</div>
  </div>

  <ul class="list-disc md:columns-5 columns-2 mx-6">
    <li>Python</li>
    <li>Java</li>
    <li>C/C++</li>
    <li>SQL</li>
    <li>PyTorch</li>
    <li>SystemVerilog</li>
    <li>React.js</li>
    <li>Flask</li>
    <li>Deep Learning</li>
    <li>LLMs & Gen AI</li>
    <li>Diffusion Models</li>
    <li>Fairness in AI</li>
    <li>Full-stack Development</li>
    <li>Database Design</li>
    <li>Git</li>
  </ul>
</BaseLayout>
